---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Telehealth Consent – QuitDr"
  description="QuitDr Telehealth Consent form and information. Understand your rights and what to expect from a telehealth consultation."
>
  <section class="page-hero" style="padding:3rem 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Telehealth Consent</h1>
      <p>What you agree to when accessing QuitDr's telehealth services.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:2rem;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal-content">
        <span class="legal-last-updated">Last updated: April 2026</span>

        <p>Before accessing a telehealth consultation with a QuitDr doctor, you are required to provide informed consent. This document explains what telehealth is, its limitations, and what you are agreeing to.</p>

        <h2>1. What is Telehealth?</h2>
        <p>Telehealth is the delivery of health care services using digital communications technology — including video calls, audio calls, and online questionnaires — where the patient and health practitioner are not in the same physical location.</p>
        <p>QuitDr uses telehealth to connect you with Australian-registered doctors for smoking cessation consultations. Your consultation may be primarily questionnaire-based, with a video or audio call if clinically required.</p>

        <h2>2. Benefits of Telehealth</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Access to a doctor from your home or workplace</li>
          <li>No need for a GP referral or in-person visit</li>
          <li>Private and confidential</li>
          <li>Convenient scheduling</li>
          <li>Faster access to smoking cessation support</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Limitations of Telehealth</h2>
        <p>Telehealth has inherent limitations compared to in-person care. By consenting to telehealth, you acknowledge:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your doctor cannot perform a physical examination</li>
          <li>The quality of the consultation may be affected by technical issues (internet connection, device performance)</li>
          <li>Some conditions may not be appropriately managed via telehealth alone</li>
          <li>If your doctor determines that in-person care is required, they will advise you accordingly</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Your Rights as a Patient</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Receive clear information about the service before consenting</li>
          <li>Ask questions about your treatment at any time</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent and end the consultation at any time</li>
          <li>Seek a second opinion from another healthcare provider</li>
          <li>Access your medical records held by QuitDr</li>
          <li>Make a complaint about the service or treating doctor</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Your Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>For a safe and effective telehealth consultation, you agree to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide accurate and complete health information in the intake form</li>
          <li>Disclose all current medications, medical conditions, and allergies</li>
          <li>Be in a private, quiet environment during the consultation</li>
          <li>Notify the doctor if your condition changes</li>
          <li>Follow your doctor's medical advice or seek further care if needed</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Privacy and Confidentiality</h2>
        <p>Your health information is handled in accordance with QuitDr's <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> and the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth). Your consultation details will not be shared with your employer or any third party except as described in the Privacy Policy (e.g. dispensing pharmacy, treating doctor).</p>

        <h2>7. Not an Emergency Service</h2>
        <p>QuitDr is not an emergency medical service. If you experience a medical emergency during or after your consultation, call <strong>000</strong> immediately. Do not use QuitDr for urgent or life-threatening conditions.</p>

        <h2>8. Recording</h2>
        <p>Telehealth consultations are not recorded by QuitDr unless you are notified in advance and have provided explicit consent to recording. You must not record your consultation without the consent of your treating doctor.</p>

        <h2>9. Technical Requirements</h2>
        <p>A video or audio consultation requires a stable internet connection and a device with a functioning camera and microphone (if a video call is required). QuitDr is not responsible for technical issues on your end that affect consultation quality.</p>

        <h2>10. Complaints</h2>
        <p>If you have a complaint about your consultation or the conduct of a doctor, you can:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Contact QuitDr support: <a href="mailto:support@quitdr.com.au">support@quitdr.com.au</a></li>
          <li>Lodge a complaint with <strong>AHPRA</strong> (Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency) at <a href="https://www.ahpra.gov.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.ahpra.gov.au</a></li>
          <li>Contact the <strong>Health Care Complaints Commission</strong> in your state or territory</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>11. Consent Confirmation</h2>
        <p>By completing the booking process and ticking the consent checkbox, you confirm that:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>You have read and understood this Telehealth Consent document</li>
          <li>You consent to receiving telehealth medical services from QuitDr</li>
          <li>You understand the limitations of telehealth compared to in-person care</li>
          <li>You understand this is a private service not covered by Medicare</li>
          <li>You are 18 years of age or older</li>
        </ul>

        <div style="margin-top:2.5rem; text-align:center;">
          <a href="/book" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Book Your $10 Consult</a>
        </div>

        <div class="compliance-box" style="margin-top:2rem;">
          <span class="icon">&#128274;</span>
          <span>This service provides general medical support for smoking cessation via telehealth. Treatments and outcomes vary between individuals. Medications are prescribed only if clinically appropriate. Please consult a healthcare professional to determine what is right for you. This is a telehealth service — not covered by Medicare.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
